The Stonehouse -- Nevada City
Majestic Historical Old Brewery, Penthouse, Office, Turn-Key Bar/Restaurant, Patios, Wine Cave, Weddings/Banquet Facility
We have 6 event area, from Cellar, Patios, Banquet Rooms to Ball Room, we can host 2-555 guests. Available for lease independently! $1-$1.25/ per S.F.
Dreaming of expanding or opening your own business?
The Stonehouse is available for you to expand or start a small or big business!
We are looking for a restaurateur or individuals who would like to relocate or open their own business. I see, an eatery, cafe, cyber cafe, spa, brewery, market place, pop up restaurant, a collective .... whatever your vision or dream?
Joint ventures are welcome! Spa? Boutique Hotel? Private Castle? Market Place? Yoga/Dance Studio? Retail? Office? Club? Whatever you can envision..
How about reviving the brewery and let the golden beer flow again? This beautiful, historic granite building was build in 1852. It is nestled in the Sierra Nevada foothills gold rush town of Nevada City, California along Little Deer Creek and the Pioneer Park Trail.
The Stonehouse opened its doors in February 2004 becoming one of the signature restaurants in the Sierra Nevada foothills. Inspiration came from the building itself, a massive, romantic, fully restored 1800´s stone and timber structure located in downtown Nevada City. Both the building and the town are listed on the National Register of Historic Places.
More info: www.facebook.com/note.php?note_id=10150199419959256
A full liquor license is available. There are lots of equipment, fixtures, furniture and inventory. This can be a turn-key operation. The Stonehouse can accommodate multiple tenants.
Whole facility:
10,800 sq.ft.
This includes all $700,000 of improvements, FF& E(Furniture, Fixture and Equipment)
1st Floor:
4,000 sq. ft.
The cozy pub has a fireplace, a beautiful, carved back bar from the 1800`s and antiques. The dining room has an open kitchen with an oven and wood-fired grill, a performance stage and a floating dance floor, great for concerts and dance club events.
2nd Floor:
4,000 sq. ft. two Banquet Rooms, one sophisticated Commercial Kitchen, 1,000 SF.
Brick Patio.
This space is divided into a 900 sq.ft. commercial kitchen with access to the Granite Room, a carpeted banquet room featuring a huge showcase wine rack, granite walls on three sides and tall, carved, gilt and painted Victorian doors. The adjacent Timber Room, located at the top of the open stair, features stone walls, timber posts and beams, a cozy alcove, and a small dance floor and is suitable for banquets, intimate weddings, and service club meetings.
3rd Floor:
2000 sq. ft
Beautiful wrap-around deck space for office, gallery, private club, cigar room, manager`s quarters, bridal suites
Stone Patio:
1200 sq.ft.
The Patio has a rock wall and cascading vines, a beautiful tree-shaded setting for outdoor dining or wedding ceremonies.
2nd Floor Patio
1000 sq. ft.
An outdoor seating area edged with beautiful brick wall and greenery, up an outside staircase leading to the Timber Room entrance.
Wine Cave or Grotto Amour
The entrance gate opens onto the stone patio. The cave is a hand-dug tunnel into the hill and connects to other secret passages through the tunnels underground opening (at the time it was built it connected to brothels in the city). It was originally a brewery lager cave, then secret passages to other areas in the city.
Basement, Cellar, Opium Den
1000 sq ft.
This is an Intimate space for a wine cellar, wine tasting or Parisian-styled speakeasy. This consists of all stone walls.
 The Terrace which consists of 2,000 SF could be developed into an outdoor gathering place. Luau, bark house . . ..
The antique fixtures and carved wooden doors are from the beautiful Kidder mansion in Grass Valley.
Construction of the Stonehouse included a storage cave dug into the hillside, used for aging casks of ale. It was accessed from inside the building, which at that time included the space which is now a patio area. The cave had been connected to other parts of the city via tunnels. Travel Channel -- Ghost Adventure has explored these secret passages.
After being vacant for more than two decades, the building was reopened as The Old Brewery with crafted beer and food. It was again renovated in 2004 and opened as the Stonehouse Restaurant (from 2004 to 2008), featuring an 1860`s back-bar from The Texas Chicken Ranch (an illegal but tolerated brothel in the State of Texas that operated from 1905 to 1973). From 2008 to 2010 it was operated as the Stonehouse Hospitality Academy, many students were trained and are still serving in the community.
Since 2010, it has been one of the Hottest Event Venues in the area! With A Full Bar, cave, two kitchens, three dance floors. The diverse space could easily be used for bar/restaurant, offices, meeting areas, classes, events, festivals. The Stonehouse is located right in the Heart of downtown Nevada City and has a full parking lot which is located by the Little Deer Creek.
